meanings.definition: To push out or force out
meanings.sent1: She outpushed the door to open it.
meanings.sent2: The strong wind outpushed the weaker gust.
meanings.sent3: The little squirrel outpushed the big squirrel to get to the acorn first.
meanings.sent4: His determination outpushed all obstacles in his way.
meanings.sent5: The water outpushed the sand as the tide came in.

meanings.definition: To surpass in pushing or forcing out
meanings.sent1: The champion outpushed all his competitors in the arm-wrestling contest.
meanings.sent2: The new machine outpushed the old one in terms of efficiency.
meanings.sent3: The tiny ant outpushed the huge beetle in moving the crumbs.
meanings.sent4: Her enthusiasm outpushed everyone else's in the group project.
meanings.sent5: The sun outpushed the clouds, shining brightly in the sky.
